<paragraph blockId="61.[151,1437,1410,1941]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,260,1807,1833]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Remarks</emphasis>
: A common offshore, pelagic species in warm temperate to tropical seas, 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": D'Aubrey" authorityYear="1964" box="[1084,1238,1807,1833]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Carcharhinidae" genus="Carcharhinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carcharhiniformes" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="falciformis">
<emphasis box="[1084,1238,1807,1833]" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">C. falciformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was not recorded in the area until the 1960s when 
<bibRefCitation author="D'Aubrey" box="[570,779,1843,1870]" firstAuthor="D'Aubrey" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" pagination="1 - 95" refId="ref96632" refString="D'Aubrey, J. D. (1964 a) Preliminary guide to the sharks found off the east coast of South Africa. South African Association for Marine Biological Research, Oceanographic Research Institute, Investigational Report, 8, 1 - 95." type="journal article" year="1964" yearSuffix="a">D’Aubrey (1964a)</bibRefCitation>
reported it from off 
<taxonomicName box="[1014,1102,1843,1869]" class="Mollusca (awaiting allocation)" family="Mollusca (awaiting allocation)" genus="Durban" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mollusca (awaiting allocation)" pageId="61" pageNumber="126" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">Durban</taxonomicName>
. It is frequently misidentified with 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Bigelow &amp; Schroeder" authorityYear="1948" box="[255,388,1879,1905]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Carcharhinidae" genus="Carcharhinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carcharhiniformes" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="obscurus">
<emphasis box="[255,388,1879,1905]" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">C. obscurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
